                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mid-18th–mid-19th century.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <desc>Careful. The handwriting remains fairly uniform throughout the manuscript and is characterized by fine, regularly shaped and
                           slightly right-sloping letters. In <ref target="#q6"/> and <ref target="#q7"/> it appears smaller and compact due to the narrower ruling lines. 
                           It becomes irregular at the end of the manuscript.</desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; groups of lines in the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1.1">Text 1.1</ref> and <ref target="#ms_i1.3">Text 1.3</ref> incipits of all other sections and subsections; 
                           the words <foreign xml:lang="gez">dǝrsān</foreign>‘homily’ and <foreign xml:lang="gez">tagśāṣ</foreign> ‘admonitions’ in <ref target="#ms_i1.2">Text 1.2</ref>; elements of
                           the punctuation signs and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
